  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Effect of engineering constraints on charged particle wall heat loads in DEMO</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-13</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• A 2D model to evaluate the effect on the heat wall load of a large number of first wall profile and plasma shapes is presented. • A model to take into account some of the 3D feature and the misalignment tolerances of a 3D engineering wall is employed. • An automatic procedure to design a 2D first wall poloidal profile which fulfils heat flux density constraints on the wall is presented. • The calculation is verified with the 3D field line tracing code PFCflux, enhanced to satisfy the power balance.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
